@kniec `--no-install-recommends` used for [this](https://ubuntu.com/blog/we-reduced-our-docker-images-by-60-with-no-install-recommends) and does not install gcc. I used build-essential package for install gcc, make and other packages for build.

ENV for apt-get can cause unexpected side effects. [Note](https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#env)

i think the more correct way is to use the golang base image
